Just a thought to my federal policy friends, we need to think out of the box!

#Covid_19

In times like this, we need to think about both individual‚Äôs personal cash and maintaining their employment. 

Remember it is easier to maintain a job than create a new one in the short term.

#Covid_19

For example, if there was a federal package that could cover 35-65% of active salary for certain business sizes and sectors WHILE adding direct cash injections cash flow could continue AND employment would be kept at least partially intact.

#Covid_19

I know there are a lot ideas flying around, but I encourage the federal government to consider picking up a larger percentage of salary costs along with direct stimulus. 

#Covid_19

2. Jobs being active are themselves important. If the labor force sheds jobs significantly, even with regular personal cash injections there will still be lag time to re-employment.

#Covid_19

1. Remember that regular, dependable cash injections are just as important as size in most situations. People need to be able to plan around their income and stress is caused most often by uncertainty.

#Covid_19

Studied universal basic income for a while now and I appreciate that direct cash stimulus is being considered, but there are some things I want folks to think about in this particularly strange economic atmosphere.

#Covid_19
